Senate President Ahmad Lawan and other principal officers yesterday met with top security officials responsible for security in the Federal Capital Territory. A statement by the Special Adviser to the Senate President on Media, Ola Awoniyi, disclosed that meeting held at his boss’ office. “We are very concerned, like all of you are, about the level of security challenges in the FCT,” Lawan was quoted as saying. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Lawan said the meeting was a follow-up to the earlier one held last week, adding that the idea was to engage those directly dealing with the security issues within the FCT. The meeting was attended by Senate Leader Yahaya Abdullahi, Deputy Senate Leader Robert Boroffice, Chief Whip Orji Uzor Kalu, Deputy Chief Whip Aliyu Sabi Abdullahi, Deputy Minority Leader Emmanuel Bwacha, Minority Whip Philip Aduda and others. Also in attendance were the National Security Adviser, Babagana Monguno, FCT Minister Mohammed Bello, Director-General of the Department of State Service Yusuf Magaji Bichi, Assistant Inspector-General of Police Peter Ogunyanwo, who represented the IGP, FCT Commissioner of Police Bala Ciroma and Permanent Secretary of FCT Administration Chinyeaka Ohaa. Senate President meets security chiefs over insecurity in FCT Lawan’s men get Senate Leader, Chief Whip, others Breaking: Lawan announces Senate's principal officers as Orji Kalu gets Chief Whip